Ask HN: Do you have weird “puzzle dreams” after a day of abstract programming?
text: Here's something I noticed about myself and later had confirmed by a few colleagues: After a day of programming abstract concepts (pure algorithms, math-heavy things etc.) my dreams are upsetting. I wouldn't strictly call them nightmares, but I dream of boxes folding into each other or cranks, pushing and pulling. My colleagues told me about similar dreams, involving gears, folding paper, pyramids, and other geometric shapes. My theory is that our brain tries to process the events of the day in a non-concrete fashion - and abstract programming gives it little to work with. But I am wondering: How widespread is this phenomenon? Do other people experience the same?

Ask HN: Where to start an international SaaS company (as a South African)
text:
I'm a South African looking to start a global tech company, but the business climate for starting a company in South Africa makes it a bad option.

What are the options for countries in which to start a business remotely? If anyone has experience they would be happy to share, I would love to hear where folks decided to found and what their experience has been?

Extra context - I'm looking at building a SaaS product where users could be anywhere in the world. I'm also currently trying to bootstrap, and so I'm not working through any VC's or similar.
